  "description": "<h2 id=\"introduction\">Introduction</h2>\n<p>Referred as \"the mini Golondrinas\", this is one of the most famous\npits of Chiapas and has now been developed as a tourist attraction.</p>\n<p>At the bottom is a small forest, a naturally protected summer nesting\narea for the sinkholeâ€™s namesake residents: thousands of cotorras, or\ngreen parrots. On the walls of the pit are several petroglyphs left by\npre-mayan civilizations.</p>\n<p>While Sima de las Cotorras is impressive any time, the best time to\nvisit is March to October, when the parrots are most numerous.</p>\n<p>There is a campsite and multiple cabins for rent next to the\nrestaurant that owns the pit.</p>\n<h2 id=\"approach\">Approach</h2>\n<p>Drive to Ocozocoautla, then to Crucero San Luis, then to Piedra\nParada. It is a bit hard to get to without a car. There are companies\nthat offer this as a guided trip (including transportation) from San\nCristobal.</p>\n<h2 id=\"descent\">Descent</h2>\n<p>The pit is a near perfect round sinkhole in the ground about 140 deep\nwith a diameter of 160 meter. From roughly October till March groups of\nparrots fly out of the abyss in the morning, hence its name. You can\nrappel down into it, and see of pre-hispanic drawings on the walls.</p>\n<p>It is rumored that killer bees nest in the walls of the pit, so if\nplanning to drop the pit is better to go on colder days.</p>\n<h2 id=\"exit\">Exit</h2>\n<p>If you rappel all the way to the bottom you'll ascend out to the\nhalway point. From there, it's a walk along the wall where you'll be\nable to see pre-Mayan pictographs.</p>\n<h2 id=\"red_tape\">Red tape</h2>\n<p>The only way to rappel Sima de las Cotorras is with the company that\nowns the land/restaurant. As of 2021, the price is 750 pesos for a\nrappel all the way to the bottom, or 550 pesos to rappel half way (and\nhike back out past the pictographs).</p>\n<h2 id=\"beta_sites\">Beta sites</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a\nhref=\"https://www.simadelascotorras.com/en\">https://www.simadelascotorras.com/en</a>\n(Official Website)</li>\n<li><a\nhref=\"http://www.turismochiapas.gob.mx/sectur/sima-de-las-cotorras\">http://www.turismochiapas.gob.mx/sectur/sima-de-las-cotorras</a></li>\n<li><a\nhref=\"http://moon.com/2010/02/sima-de-las-cotorras-near-tuxtla-gutierrez/\">http://moon.com/2010/02/sima-de-las-cotorras-near-tuxtla-gutierrez/</a></li>\n<li><a\nhref=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sima_de_las_Cotorras\">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sima_de_las_Cotorras</a></li>\n<li><a\nhref=\"http://todochiapas.mx/2012/04/sima-de-las-cotorras-chiapas/\">http://todochiapas.mx/2012/04/sima-de-las-cotorras-chiapas/</a></li>\n<li><a\nhref=\"http://www.explorachiapas.com/caving.html\">http://www.explorachiapas.com/caving.html</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"trip_reports_and_media\">Trip reports and media</h2>\n<h2 id=\"background\">Background</h2>\n",
